<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910314-0043</DOCNO><DOCID>910314-0043.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- PPG Industries Inc.:   Company Sees Sharp Drop   In First-Quarter Earnings</HL><DATE>03/14/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7</SO><CO>   PPG</CO><IN>DIVERSIFIED INDUSTRIAL (IDD)</IN><LP>   PPG Industries Inc., buffeted by the downturn in theautomotive and construction industries, said it expects itsfirst-quarter profit to fall as much as 50%.   In the year-ago first quarter, the Pittsburgh maker ofcoatings, glass and fibers earned $125.3 million, or $1.16 ashare. PPG said its first-quarter net would include aone-time gain from accounting changes, but the companydeclined to say how much that gain would be.</LP><TEXT>   PPG is considered a consistent earnings performer, even intough times. But the company's unexpected disclosureyesterday could augur similar earnings surprises forcompanies in basic industry. &quot;We're going to see a lot offirst-quarter disasters,&quot; predicted analyst Saul Ludwig, whofollows the company for Roulston andamp; Co. in Cleveland.   PPG, however, also indicated that economic conditions maynot have been the only cause for its weak first quarter. Thecompany said it would record charges for the realignment ofvarious operations, but declined to elaborate.</TEXT></DOC>